gomodel:SYNGO_2676  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1: \"c-Abl is present in synaptic sites in cultured hippocampal neurons\"\n- \"To test whether c-Abl is present at synaptic sites in cultured neurons, we examined the colocalization with the presynaptic marker Syn I. As observed in Figure 1B, at 14 DIV, c-Abl clusters are apposed closely to Syn I puncta, suggesting that this kinase is mainly distributed postsynaptically (Fig. 1B) as reported previously in hippocampal Schaffer collateral-CA1 synapse (Moresco et al., 2003)...Along the dendritic shaft, we observed that GFP-c-Abl-WT clusters colocalize with PSD-95 puncta in close apposition to Syn I (Fig. 1C). The Mander's overlap coefficient (R) shows that c-Abl distribution presents a higher overlap degree with PSD-95 rather than Syn I (RPSD-95 = 0.6343 ± 0.01 vs RSyn I = 0.3517 ± 0.02). These results strongly suggest that c-Abl is mainly localized on postsynaptic structures.\"\n\nFig.4: \"c-Abl interacts with PSD-95\"\n- \"The immunoprecipitation with anti-c-Abl antibody followed by PSD-95 immunoblot showed that this postsynaptic scaffold protein forms part of a complex with c-Abl and NR1 (Fig. 4A)\"\n- \"c-Abl is enriched in synaptosomal and PSD fractions from adult rat brain (Fig. 4C), validating the postsynaptic distribution of c-Abl in vivo\"\n- \"In total brain homogenate and synaptosomal fraction 1, c-Abl was coimmunoprecipitated with PSD-95 and vice versa (Fig. 4D).\". Experimental description: - \"Rat hippocampal cultures were prepared as described...\"\n- \"For postsynaptic density (PSD) isolation, the method of Carlin et al. (1980) was slightly modified. Briefly, the telencephalon of 10 male Sprague Dawley rats were dissected...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-26" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2676" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

